- Despite positives: CD 1 does score positively on concise arrangements, tight drums/bass and preserved dynamics (which I like), but those benefits don’t overcome the compilation format and the relative lack of the analog/piano/textural elements that align more closely with my top priorities (cohesive CD sequencing, warm analogue textures, and band‑centered mixes).
In sum, CD 2 better satisfies the combination of album sequencing, analogue warmth, preserved dynamics, textural instrumentation (piano/acoustics), and band‑anchored, revealing mixes that I prize — while CD 1 falls short due to its compilation nature and guitar‑forward emphasis.

